# Module

## One exported function per file

- Each function, hook, or component should live in its **own file**.
- Do not stack multiple exported helpers in one module. Extract even **small helpers** to their own files.
- File names should match the export (e.g. `fetchUser.ts` exports `fetchUser`).

## Reusable utilities → `src/lib/utils/<topic>/` (extension) / `ui/src/lib/utils/<topic>/` (webview)

- When logic is generic and reusable, place it under `src/lib/utils/<category>/` or `ui/src/lib/utils/<category>/`.
- Import utilities via the project alias, e.g. `#/lib/utils/date/formatDate`.
